## v2-specific guidance (Verocity)

### What this project is
A strength/training logger rebuilt on **Astro + React islands**, **Supabase**
(Postgres + Auth + RLS + Realtime + Edge Functions), deployed on **Vercel**
(static/edge), with **Railway** reserved for future heavy/scheduled jobs. See
`docs/SPEC.md` for the full spec.

### Architecture rules (do not violate)
- **Keep Vercel light.** The browser talks directly to Supabase. Do not add Vercel
  serverless/edge functions on the authenticated hot path — Vercel mostly serves
  static assets. AI/heavy work goes to Supabase Edge Functions or Railway.
- **Islands, not a SPA.** Use Astro static pages; hydrate React only where
  interaction is required (`client:load`/`client:visible`). The Logger is one large
  self-contained island — avoid many tiny islands.
- **RLS is the security boundary.** The anon key is public; never rely on the UI to
  enforce read-only. **Private by default:** authenticated users read AND write only
  their own rows (`owner_user_id = auth.uid()`); the shared movement library
  (`owner_user_id IS NULL`) is the only ambient cross-user read. Anon gets
  SELECT-only on the showcase profile. Cross-user sharing is explicit via
  read-only share tokens served by the `share-read` Edge Function.
- **Never ship the service-role key to the client.** It lives only in Edge
  Functions / Railway env.
- **Preserve the JSONB contracts** (`plans.parsed` = ParsedPlan,
  `workout_logs.data` = LogDocument) so logic ports cleanly.

### Conventions
- Domain config in a single `app.config.ts` (ported) — no hardcoded constants in
  components.
- HSL design tokens only; no raw colors in components. Swiss-minimalist identity
  (Clash Display + Satoshi, hairlines, tabular numbers, sharp corners, dark mode).
- TypeScript strict; types in `lib/types.ts`.

